Place half of the potatoes in a greased 2-qt. baking dish. Top with bacon, eggs and remaining potatoes. In a saucepan, combine the soup, milk, onion and peppers. Cook over medium heat until heated through. Pour over the potatoes. Cover and bake at 350 degrees F for 20 minutes. Uncover; sprinkle with cheese. Bake 10-15 minutes longer or until heated through.